 Well, I've seen most of the endings.  Here they are, as I remember them (
accuracy of quotes is pretty bad):

 Blanka (Man-beast thing):  A short woman comes forward, as a dialogue goes on
like this:

Woman: "Are you my long lost Jimmy?"
Blanka: "Huh?"
"My Jimmy was lost long ago in a plane crash over Brazil."
"My name is Blanka.  I don't know what you're talking about."
[Blanka starts to leave, but the woman is  pleasantly surprised, and shouts]
"Look!  That bracelet on your ankle!  I gave you that when you were just a little
boy!"
"Mommy!"
"Jimmy!"
[Blanka and his mom hug and cry]

 Guile (Marine Soldier type):  He takes up Bison, and prepares to kill him.  Then,
he hears a female voice behind him:

"Wait!  Don't kill him."
"Amy?  Is that my little Amy?"
"Yes, daddy."
"But...But I left you years ago."
"You've proven that you're not the little shrimp you used to be.  You'll be no
better than he is if you kill him."
"..."
"Let's start over.  You me and mom, together again."  (Yes, her mother is here
too, but I really don't remember this ending at all)
[Fade to black---Fade in again with Guile sitting in a chair with Amy and her
mom, in his house, smoking a pipe]
"What is it, dear?" Amy's mom asks him (I don't remember her name)
"Oh.  Nothing.  It just all seems like a dream."

E. Honda (Sumo Wrestler):
[Fade in with E. Honda sitting in front of several students, all eating]
"You see.  With proper training and discipline, you can asccomplish anything.
Eat."
(Again, I don't remember this ending well)

Dhalsim (Indian Rubber-Man):
[Fade in as Dhalsim rides an elephant home.  Dhalsim fades in again at home some
time later]
"Who's that?" says a little boy, pointing to a picture of Dhalsim.
"Oh.  Just your father in another life."

Chun Li (Only female fighter):
[Fade in to a remorseful Chun Li hunched over a grave]
(Paraphrasing of quotes here for understanding)
"Now, father, I have avenged your death.  Bison's drug ring will break up.  And
now, you may rest in peace..."
[Fade in to a Chun Li running joyfully away]
"...and I can get on with my life as a single, young girl."

Ken (Blonde karate master):
[A Barbie-looking doll walks onscreen]
"Ken?"
(Don't remember her name---using Barbie :&) ) "Barbie?"
"How did you find me?"
"I just had to come see you."
[Fade in to a scene of Ken holding Barbie.  Suddenly, they are in wedding clothes]

Ryu (Japanese karate master):
[Fade in to awards ceremony with Bison 2nd, Sagat 3rd, blank 1st place pedastol]
(commentator) "Where is Ryu?  Where is he, even as his fans are chanting his
name? "
[fade in to a picture of Ryu walking into the sunset]
"Already seeking the next challenge.  Awards are nothing to him.  The fight is
all."

Zangief (Russian Wrestler):
[Helicopter hangs over Zangief, with Gorbechov on a ladder from the helicopter]
"Comrade Zangief, you have made your country proud.  You have shown that the
Soviet spirit is indominitable.  Now, let us celebrate in the typical Russian
fashion."
[Fade in to Zangief, Gorbechov and several secret service men dancing]
"You dance very well, Mr. President."
"Thank you, comrade.  It helps me to stay in shape."

Hope those were at least a bit accurate (NOT).


